   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "This PR creates a new ZMQ notifier that gives a \"total hash history\" of block (dis)connection, mempool addition/substraction, all in one pipeline. It also exposes a \"mempool sequence number\" to both this notifier and `getrawmempool` results, which allows the consumer to use the results together without confusion about ordering of results and without excessive `getrawmempool` polling.\r\n\r\nSee the functional test `interfaces_zmq.py::test_mempool_sync` which shows the proposed user flow for the client-side tracking of mempool contents and confirmations.\r\n\r\nAlternative to https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19462#issuecomment-658304417 due to noted deficiencies in current zmq notification streams.\r\n\r\nAlso fixes a legacy zmq test that didn't actually trigger a reorg because of identical blocks being generated on each side of the split(oops)\r\n",
